<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-17T09:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-17T09:45:00-05:00" n="517" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/248: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-17T09:00:00-05:45">February 17, 1934—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>55. My 51, February 16, noon.<note n="16" xml:id="d517fn16">Not
                                printed.</note> The President showed me yesterday telegram sent last
                            night to Ubico requesting latter to accede to slight postponement
                            requested by Costa Rica.</p>
                        <p>Private secretary has just telephoned me that Ubico’s reply states that
                            arrangement will be acceptable to Guatemala.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Central American mission[s].</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>